e 239 158", "bbox": [73.4, 559.8, 693.2, 572.1]}, {"text": "positive 239 247 positive 214 221", "bbox": [170.7, 588.1, 693.1, 600.2]}, {"text": "sensitivity 63.8 sensitivity 58.3", "bbox": [152.7, 616.2, 607.7, 628.3]}, {"text": "specificity 46.3 specificity 52.8", "bbox": [152.7, 629.2, 607.7, 641.2]}, {"text": "Table 3 compares each SWT (systolic wall thickening) score at baseline and follow-up through cross tabulation with the segments in CMR showing", "bbox": [73.4, 657.2, 690.5, 669.3]}, {"text": "LGE (late enhancement). Sensitivity and specificity were calculated through cross tabulation.", "bbox": [73.4, 669.0, 461.2, 681.0]}, {"text": "Table 4: Transmurality and SWT", "bbox": [68.4, 722.2, 224.4, 734.1]}, {"text": "Transmurality Number of segments Mean SWT ± SE Statistical difference to group 2 Statistical difference to group 3", "bbox": [73.4, 744.9, 683.0, 757.1]}, {"text": "(< 50%) (> 50%)", "bbox": [357.3, 756.6, 566.2, 768.8]}, {"text": "group 1: 0 448 63.6% ± 20.4% n.s. p < 0.001", "bbox": [73.4, 784.7, 570.4, 796.9]}, {"text": "group 2: < 50% 59 50.44% ± 48.7% x n.s.", "bbox": [73.4, 797.6, 544.0, 809.8]}, {"text": "group 3: > 50% 325 50.08% ± 20.0% n.s. x", "bbox": [73.4, 810.5, 535.5, 822.7]}, {"text": "In order to detect differences between the transmural extent of the infarct and changes of SWT (systolic wall thickening), we made three groups", "bbox": [73.4, 838.8, 685.6, 850.9]}, {"text": "according to their transmurality (first had no transmurality, second had less than 50%, and the third had more than 50% transmurality). In the acute", "bbox": [73.4, 850.5, 690.5, 862.5]}, {"text": "state of myocardial infarction we detected a highly significant difference in SWT between the first group with no scar and group 3 (p < 0.001).", "bbox": [73.4, 862.1, 672.6, 874.2]}, {"text": "Within the groups there could not be detected any difference regarding SWT and transmurality. There could not be detected any difference", "bbox": [73.4, 873.9, 666.3, 885.9]}, {"text": "between group 1 and group 2. n.s. = not significant, SE = standard error. ANOVA with Bonferroni post-hoc testing was used for statistical analysis.", "bbox": [73.4, 885.5, 693.2, 897.6]}, {"text": "Page 6 of 10", "bbox": [634.0, 953.2, 698.3, 968.9]}, {"text": "(page number not for citation purposes)", "bbox": [543.8, 969.9, 698.4, 981.8]}]}